g.text: EleanorRank2Convo2 begins.

g.title: j971909630
g.text: How did you end up here in Höllvania?

g.title: j2254399150
g.text: What was it like growing up with Arthur?

g.title: j942936509
g.text: Long story.

g.title: j4169925466
g.text: Idyllic. We never fought, not even once. We kept one another’s secrets. He even let me braid his hair.

g.title: j3294373884
g.text: Should I even bother asking? Or is this a conversation better suited for later?

g.title: j773400279
g.text: Are you going to give me the real version?

g.title: j3790297114
g.text: No wonder everyone else is jealous of me and wants Arthur to be their brother, too.

g.title: j2891161856
g.text: Later, assuming you haven't skipped town and I haven't mutated into a raging shapeless wad of muscle tissue and mouths.

g.title: j937707233
g.text: Perhaps, once I’m sure you won’t go running back and forth between Arthur and me, comparing notes.

g.title: j1034920554
g.text: I bet he let you practice makeup on him, too.

g.title: j2130610442
g.text: How nice. [End.]

g.title: j4276761805
g.text: Because you might learn things about certain people that you might find hard to stomach.

g.title: j2160222113
g.text: I can’t imagine he’s opened up to you much.

g.title: j2270852384
g.text: Actually, he did do that. Until quite recently, in fact.

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j3876682861
g.text: Aren't I cryptic? Like a Sphinx. Rarr.

g.title: j1134481298
g.text: He’s quite a private guy, yeah.

g.title: j858111432
g.text: I wish he would wear eyeliner more often. He claims it’s too much of a faff. Prefers burnt cork.

g.title: j2773125233
g.text: Arthur thinks there are some things you shouldn’t talk about. He’s old-fashioned like that. ‘Bad for morale’, he’ll say. ‘Camp chatter.’ ‘Careful, might be circulating enemy propaganda.’

g.title: j288395895
g.text: The smudgy dark-eyed look does suit him, but he doesn’t know when to stop with the eyeshadow. He tries to be a moody stubble god, all folded arms and 2am bus stops, but then he keeps going and ends up as a hungover emo panda. And he wonders why people don’t take him seriously.

g.title: j2046880269
g.text: Always the soldier. Is he ever NOT on duty?

g.title: j3561361185
g.text: Boolean EleanorArthurPanda is now true.

g.title: j1072261442
g.text: Oh, it runs deep in our family.

g.title: j586350804
g.text: I don't know, I think he's pretty sexy... for a hungover emo panda.

g.title: j2276949608
g.text: I'd let you practice makeup on me if you wanted. ;)

g.title: j617923408
g.text: I’m having trouble taking YOU seriously.

g.title: j1753541494
g.text: Dad used to have an old Army poster from the ‘37 Bombardment on the wall in the downstairs loo. A square-jawed loyal soldier is punching out a scrawny moaner whose glasses go flying off. Caption: “Slap the chap who flaps his trap with crap!”

g.title: j1155720075
g.text: That is entirely your prerogative and I will not judge you for your choice

g.title: j2819197595
g.text: HOW DARE YOU

g.title: j4290821066
g.text: Which is just what I want.

g.title: j714919242
g.text: Arthur loved it because it was ‘rude’. He took its lesson to heart, though. ‘Don’t talk about things that could hurt the people we care about.’

g.title: j2787331186
g.text: I will even wish you happy hunting, if you are so inclined

g.title: j2848750438
g.text: Do not disparage the sacred ritual that is Doing One Another's Makeup

g.title: j514558578
g.text: Give him a break. It’s good sense, for a fighting team. You can’t sail a leaky ship.

g.title: j2588847413
g.text: That's not right. If you don't talk about hurtful things, you just... bottle it up.

g.title: j554724395
g.text: HOWEVER

g.title: j2784539864
g.text: We are not even close to being well enough acquainted for that.

g.title: j2475681035
g.text: All very well until it’s being invoked to shut you up.

g.title: j326895373
g.text: And if you bottle it up, it can spiral out of control. ... I have some experience with that...

g.title: j2206736330
g.text: If I suspect FOR ONE INSTANT that you are using anything I choose to share with you as leverage to get into his armoured pants...

g.title: j3466876691
g.text: Sorry, let me just catch my breath a moment.

g.title: j924433462
g.text: All my life there have been things we NEEDED to talk about. There are conversations we SHOULD have had. Granny Callie. Christopher. The Cavona Mansion. They festered between us.

g.title: j3263520813
g.text: Precisely. It's all very well and good until it's being invoked to shut you up.

g.title: j1724820725
g.text: ... I will be every inch the monster people think I am, for long enough to make you wish you were back in the execution circus.

g.title: j4034031626
g.text: ... I'm not saying never. Okay? And it only just occurred to me that this might be the first time, for you.

g.title: j483437737
g.text: But no. Talking about it was Simply Not Done. Too much at stake.

g.title: j674051346
g.text: Boolean EleanorArthurHunt is now true.

g.title: j387797361
g.text: So I'll give you a pass, this once. But in all seriousness, it's not the sort of thing to joke about.

g.title: j1472054875
g.text: So because the alternative was never to feel clean in my own skin again, I made it my business to find out about other things that people didn’t want talked about, and I talked about them. I wrote about the kinds of things that soon had people trying to nudge my car over the edge of a Hibernian mountain pass.

g.title: j2158115
g.text: It meant a lot for Arthur to trust me like that. It meant even more that I was able to make him feel genuinely good about himself.

g.title: j3064367048
g.text: Remember, I’m not from here. What things?

g.title: j905121357
g.text: Hibernian what now?

g.title: j695023695
g.text: Blimey. I feel like owe you an apology now, and I don't really do those.

g.title: j3588318156
g.text: The usual stuff. Corruption at the highest levels of government. Paternity scandals in the Höllvanian royal family. Tainted milk powder being distributed to nursing mothers in ‘undesirable’ sink estates in New Holywell.

g.title: j2713445864
g.text: Right, yes. Tourist to our time. The usual stuff. Corruption at the highest levels of government. Paternity scandals in the Höllvanian royal family. Tainted milk powder being distributed to nursing mothers in ‘undesirable’ sink estates in New Holywell.

g.title: j1123333353
g.text: +15 Chemistry

g.title: j3631958017
g.text: Because when someone tells you to shut up, you do not comply, EVER.

g.title: j1617188351
g.text: Let's chalk this one up to experience, eh?

g.title: j1570221963
g.text: You remind me of Nora Night.

g.title: j4248651869
g.text: I agree.

g.title: j4205890645
g.text: Boolean EleanorHasFlirted is now true.

g.title: j3807808261
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j1117620150
g.text: +15 Chemistry

g.title: j688061513
g.text: I assume that’s a good thing? Tell me about her some time when I’m not in the mood to rip someone’s head off.

g.title: j2924177329
g.text: Anyway. Arthur wanted me to shut up, for the good of the family. Now I don’t talk at all. Yet for some reason Arthur’s still not happy.

g.title: j4182512264
g.text: I ask you. What is a sister to do?
